						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">NMI begin:<br />1 - read controllers<br />2 - game logic<br />3 - OAM DMA<br />4 - scroll<br />5 - game clock (just 16-bit increment to a reserved ram location)<br />6 - famitone update<br />7 - RTI</div><br />This is an awful idea. VRAM updates and OAM DMA must happen during the short VBlank time, which happens directly after NMI.</div>

