				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A little bird told me about an official document mentioning that DMA must begin within 286uS of beginning of NMI (which is about 512 CPU cycles, I think), or &quot;there may be a problem with the DMA transfer&quot;.  I always thought it was sensible to do the DMA early as possible, but it seems that it's actually required.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
