					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh by the way I forgot to address that:<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">How can double dragon 1 sometimes take 11 frames to react? </div><br />Double Dragon games uses the button combination A+B to jump. It is almost impossible to require for the player to press those buttons at the same time, so when the game detect that A or B is pressed, very likely it waits a few frames to see if the player press the other button, if yes then the main character jumps, if no then it punches or kicks. 11 frames still sounds like quite a lot, are sure sure it's not less ? I'd say it's probably about 5 frames, although this must be verified. Also, one frame delay is compulsory because there's one frame delay between when the game decides to run the logic and when it's actually shown on screen.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

